data.description: This is a great opportunity to own an affordable pool home that has recent updates including kitchen, baths, roof and the electric system. This home offers space inside and out. The interior has an open floor plan while the fenced back yard is over sized. The interior features laminate flooring for easy maintenance, newer kitchen cabinets and stone counters along with remodeled bathrooms. The living room is open to the kitchen allowing everyone to live together throughout the day. The kitchen was remodeled in 2019/2020 with new, raised-panel, antique-white cabinets topped with beautiful granite counters, black and stainless steel Frigidaire appliances, neutral stone-like ceramic tile, a designer faucet and deep sink, recessed lighting in the ceiling and a beautiful glass-tile mosaic back splash. The lower kitchen cabinets include a lazy Susan, pull out pot drawers and all of the cabinets have crystal-like door pulls further enhancing the antique styling of times past. Your laundry room is between the garage and the kitchen giving you extra space for storage and convenience to load and unload shopping bags. The owners’ suite includes a walk-in closet and a pampered bathroom finished in grey’s and white marble tile. The shower is absolutely beautiful! All of the bedrooms have ceiling fans. There is no carpeting in this home making your life more simple! The family room has French doors to the patio and pool area. The garage has extra space and cabinets helping you to stay organized. The back yard is fenced and has a lot of room to play. At 1/3 acre, this yard gives you endless possibilities for use and enjoyment. Relaxing poolside all summer long will be hit with friends and family! Your screened patio offers year round outdoor comfort. Both sides of the fence are gated giving you convenient access to the rear. There is a small storage shed along with a cement slab perfect for an additional structure or patio. Your daily commute is shortened since I-4 and I-75 are nearby. Shopping, dining, post office, schools and the Seffner Public Library are just minutes away. The Seffner Civic Center and Park is directly across the street making life even more enjoyable for you and the kids. There is no HOA or deed restrictions to limit your lifestyle. The roof was replaced in 2018. The electric service panel was replaced recently too. Call today and schedule your private tour!
